			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In Chinese culture, there is a tradition that when several people are having a dinner in a restaurant, there is always one person who is going to pay for it. That is very different from Western culture where in most cases everyone will pay for himself/herself.<br />
This lesson covers most of the vocabulary you can use in conversations when you want to buy someone a dinner or if someone wants to invite you. Please sign up and become a registered subscriber to download ALL 200+ audio lessons with full PDF transcripts and worksheets.</p>
